Okay so I NEED you to save this right mow and next time you’re working out you’re going to press play and let me take you through this entire lower body follow along warm up segment. 

I’m going to get you ready for your session safely and effectively whether you’re training at home or in the gym I’m literally with you ❗️

SAVE NOW and let me know if you want to see more 👇

node.title: FOLLOW ALONG LOWER BODY ACTIVATION/ WARM UP 🔥

node.text:
Now look.... you might be thinking is all this necessary and my reply is YES. I recently uploaded a full leg day workout on my YouTube to which I showcased a comprehensive lower body dynamic warm up, the warm up took no longer than 5-8mins.

I read a comment that said “I don’t believe you spend this long to warm up it seems excessive” and to which I said “well after 7 years of training I’ve not had one injury nor the clients I’ve trained one on one??”

Moral of the story... you want longevity in your fitness journey. THEN MOBILISE YOUR BODY AND STOP SKIPPING YOUR WARM UPS ❗️❗️

I am a trainer that’s what I love to do train myself and people so whilst I might come off as a little blunt your longevity and well-being means more to me than an extra rep and set you do!

node.title: You want longevity but you’re not willing to spend time to warm up ❗️👀

node.text:
Here in the UK things are opening back up and I want to stress the importance of going at your own pace! 

I designed and built the @toneandsculptapp to be compatible for home or gym. With over 1 million rounds and nearly 1million SCULPT IT! Workouts being completed by women in the comfort of their own homes and bright smiles every single time they smashed a workout I think it’s safe to say the objective is to move your body in a way that feels good to you in a place that feels right for you!

I love the gym but I also love my home workouts in my avocado PJs listening to James brown! Either way do what YOU WANT not what others are doing.

Hope this helps 💙

node.text:
I’m drained.... like I’m truly truly drained today and I’ll tell you why. I am so upset that women still feel that the scales are determining so much of their happiness. I’m so upset that you feel the need to justify your weight in order to show your success when really you should be so proud of everything you have achieved in your journey so far.

I used to HATE myself I used to step on scales every single day (a set of white scales my mum had at home under the bathroom sink) and I used to eat less in order to lose more. 

I now weight nearly 10kg (give or take 22lbs) more than I did when I started my journey and The ONLY numbers I SOMETIMES use to determine longevity of success is maybe being able to lift more over time. 

I want you to SHOW UP FOR YOU! Not for the scales! I want you to try and give me one more rep if you can, one more smile at the end of a workout even if you hate me after a workout I made you do! I want you to be proud of the discipline you’re building and allow that to be your determination of success NOT THE SCALES! 

Trust me I’ve been there! I really really have so I understand you more than you’ll ever believe! 

I’m proud of you for getting this far it’s time you truly start to feel proud of YOU 💙

I might not be Muslim myself but this is absolutely irrelevant because I’m here to help everyone as much as I possible can.

Last year you loved my post on Ramadan so I truly hope this helps! 

I’ll be providing a free “breaking fast” workout on my Facebook at 22nd April 9:15pm GMT COMPLETELY FREE ❗️

Myself and the @toneandsculptapp have put together a comprehensive blog post with our incredible girl @zahara.chowdhury to help you during this special time (on the T&as website now) ❗️

https://toneandsculpt.app/blogs/lifestyle/can-i-exercise-during-ramadan

node.title: Ramadan & Working out. Last year we touched base so here we are 💙

Introducing one of your KEY exercises for the @toneandsculptapp BEAT YOUR BEST CHALLENGE: the goblet squat 

If you know me you know as your trainer and bestie (bestie first) I have a big BIGA THING about form! It’s literally what I love understanding the most

When I was gaining my personal training qualification I actually wished we was taught more on foundational moves and form executions and would read articles on top of my studies to learn more and more! 

Form is EVERYTHING so please listen, take note and come back to this video whenever you feel confused on how to perfect your goblet squat! 

Send this to a friend who might need help ⭐️

node.text:
I have never believed in anything more than when I started the @toneandsculptapp I remember my initial idea “bringing like minded women to one platform to help them with their fitness journey whilst making friends for life” a place we felt welcomed, loved, celebrated.

Looking back now its insane to think that 142 countries world wide tune in daily to complete their workouts and encourage one another! One of those members is our girl MEL! Mel is one of the youngest T&S users and members. She has been through so much in her life and has found her sense of belongness here with all of us!💙

Some may wonder why I showcase so much of our community and truth is its not that I have to its that I WANT TO CELEBRATE YOU! I have a platform to educates, encourage and push YOU that’s what ill always be here for!

I found out is was Mens B day from our @toneandsculptapp Ambassadors and well… the rest is history.

I love and adore you Mel! You are truly a shining star. @mellghewitt

node.title: THIS IS WHY I LOVE BEING YOUR TRAINER 💙

node.text:
Here is an insane transformation using the @toneandsculptapp by our community member @autumnsollerss ⭐️

I had the pleasure of speaking to our girl back in June last year where she literally wore her beautiful heart on her sleeve and told me about her struggles her personal battles and how much she wanted to make a change. It was a story we can all relate to; binge eating, unhappiness and never doing anything for herself. 

Fast forward to today and I see a woman who has literally changed her entire life MENTALLY and PHYSICALLY! And I am so honoured to have you as part of our global 🌎 community! 

The @toneandsculptapp is life changing and I mean that with every fibre in my body! It gives you purpose, confidence and support to hit your goals and DO THIS FOR YOU! 

Download it, try it, it’s free for 14 days if you don’t like it unsubscribe ! But at least try it and commit for a week to something 💙 #toneandsculpt

node.text:
BOOTY & HAMMIES 🔥

Like / Save & Enjoy (kinda) 

Where are all my strong program @toneandsculptapp community members at for real!!!! The results, the progress, the love and hype you are giving the strong program is unmatched ! So happy you’re enjoying it.

I split leg days into; Glute & Hammies / Quads & Calfs if you’re doing the 5 day a week program ❗️I’ve just posted an entire leg workout on my YouTube channel you can try with me explaining each and every single exercise! 

METHOD:

✅ Sumo Dead’s: 12/12/10/10/8/6 reps 

✅Dead stop hip thrust: 10/10/8/6/6

✅Sumo DB lift into sumo pulse: 10 reps and 15 reps 3 sets 

✅DB stiff-leg Deadlift:12x4 

IGNORE THE REPS ON TGE VIDEO!!! Do the reps on the caption 

Compounds, isolations, hinge movements, volume and unilateral…. We are doing all types of progressive overload with my strong guide.

Give this workout ago and I hope you enjoy it and find it easy to follow! Remember for a full vocal explanation head on over to my YouTube and let me train you 💙

Outfit; @oneractive 🔥

node.text:
DO YOU DO CARDIO BEFORE OR AFTER WEIGHTS❓

I want to make it clear that as a trainer this is MY personal preferences and what I would advise my community to do and what I do myself, everyone is different so let’s keep this in mind. 

The way I view it is; to get the most out of your workout and performance, perform the exercise that is most important to your goals first. This is when you’re least fatigued and tired. 

✅If you’re priority is to increase strength the presumption is you want to lift as heavy as you can with good/ safe form therefore you want to focus your energy on priorities this specific goal, cardio would come last.

Mentally you require a lot of resilience, focus and energy getting ready to lift and most of the time if you’ve spent 30 mins doing cardio before strength training your brains already a little fatigued too. 

✅If you’re priority is “losing weight” and not necessarily fussed about building strength (beating personal bests) then your goal is different to the above and therefore so would your structure. 

If you’re doing the strong guide on the @toneandsculptapp I would advise doing cardio at the end due to the compound lifts I’ve asked you to do or even splitting your cardio and strength training sessions! 

I hope this helps let me know 👇

ARMS & ABS 🔥

Like / Save / Hope this helps ⭐️

It’s the last week of the Elevate Challenge on the @toneandsculptapp and one of the workouts was “abs and arms” which I know a lot of ladies found a little difficult which is super understandable. Upper body strength for some of us can be our “weakness” but I want you to take some time to invest in improving your strength overtime! Give this workout ago! 

METHOD:

✅ Alternating Bicep Curls: amazing single arm movement and great for muscular imbalance 

✅ DB PUSH UP: when performing a diamond push up you’ll target your triceps more. drop to your knees if you find this too difficult. DB will help any wrist pain!

✅ DB CURL INTO EXTENSION: a great complex  to try if short on time ! 

✅ PLANK ELBOW TO KNEE: super intense abs movement that requires a lot of control so ensure your hips do not drop to the floor !

✅ SIDE PLANK CRUNCHES: If you want it more advanced pivot on your toes and avoid having a knee bent!

Save this workout to try later! 

Wearing: @oneractive Classic Seamless

node.text:
Home Guide Transformation using the @toneandsculptapp !🔥

Our community member @tirzah.a.wethern has absolutely smashed her goals and home workout and I couldn’t be prouder ⭐️! 

As always I like to remind you that a transformation is simply a by-product of the mental resilience each one of our community members have achieved! The constant grind, consistency and “can do attitude” !! 

Smashed it my girl! Smashed the home guide and I’m so proud !!! 

Link in bio to come and join the #toneandsculptapp community today ❗️

node.text:
I’ve had a platform now on social for I’d say about 4-5 years. I’ve learnt difficult lessons along the way, met some incredible people and built an unmatched community….. a community of women who are so inspiring and so captivating I thank god everyday for the community we have. 

During my time on social I’ve realised how much comparison there is…. Daily! From women and I may of even added to that comparison! Therefore I made the decision this year to step down as CEO of our company @toneandsculptapp and focus more on community and being the best trainer, support system and overall friend I could. Part of what I promised myself is to be open about how I’m feeling, not for sympathy, not for likes, not for attention, but to purely remind you that I, like you, am I human being and deal with a ton of ups and down OFTEN. 

You and I deal with stress, anxiety, confusion, overthinking, procrastination and even depression at time and it’s OKAY to feel these things, it’s okay to talk opening about these things. How can you work on your body if you’re not even investing in bettering your mind? 

I have made the decision as of late to see a therapist, to talk to someone, to be open about my emotions in hopes of helping 1 more person feel connected, feel safe here and to encourage you to look after you. There is nothing to be ashamed of! There is nothing weak about you! This is a journey and I’ll be dammed if I shy away from telling you how I genuinely feel because some fool thinks it’s for sympathy rather than understanding it’s what every single human feels on a daily, weekly, monthly basis.

I cry, I feel drained, I feel so confused and have self doubt a lot. I let past trauma define me too often and that’s why I keep pushing you to DO THIS FOR YOU! Work on you for you! Only you. 

You got this…. Remember it’s okay not to be okay it will make you stronger. 💙

node.text:
STRONG GUIDE LEG WORKOUT ⭐️

from the @toneandsculptapp that left my legs feeling like absolute jelly ! You will be familiar with all these movements if you’re doing the strong program 3 or 5 days a eeek ladies! Link in bio to start your program today. 

WORKOUT: 

✅ Back Squats: 90kg (198lbs) this was my final sets at 6 reps 

✅ Split Squats: 25kg (55lbs) 15 Reps 3 sets 

✅ Sumo Squat: 50kg (110lbs) 12 Reps 4 sets 

✅ Leg Press: 10/10/8/8/6 170kg in plates (374lbs) 

✅ SLD: 50kg (110lbs) 12 Reps 4 Sets 

Just a small reminder these are my personal weight, it’s taken years of training so do not compare me to your journey currently. Utilise this post as a positive not a comparison and know your Potential is sky high….. even if people want to “chat shit” you got to stay focused and work on you for you! 

Strong guide available now ! Link in bio ❗️#legworkout #gymgirl #gymworkout

MORNING MOCHA COFFEE SMOOTHIE 🔥

If you’re in a rush or need a quick pick me up fully of nutrition and support then try this recipe from the @toneandsculptapp which is delicious!

RECIPE: 

✅ 1 Cup Milk 
✅ Espresso Shot 
✅ @womensbest fudge brownie protein available now on GNC 
✅ 1 Cup Oats 
✅ 1tsp of peanut butter

Blend together and enjoy! Add ice as well to make it super creamy and cold.

node.text:
A transformation picture goes beyond physical change, it’s simply a by-product of the constant efforts someone has made to better themselves for themselves.

This post is one it a little difficult to make and whilst I hope it helps anyone that reads it, I can’t help but feel so exposed. 

The woman on the left who weighed 49kg (whilst some may prefer the “before” and that’s down to opinion) had obsessive eating habits, made it seem to the world she was okay when really she would have major food anxiety every time she went out for a meal with friends and family. Would count everything that went into her body and became addicted to cardio and training. Whilst on the outside I looked “good” to others on the inside I had server body dysmorphia. 

It has taken me years to overcome that mentality and to appreciate what my body is designed to really do….. keep me safe, protected, moving and to enjoy life whilst getting strong and stronger. Health is not a joke to me, it’s not a quick fix trend, it’s not a Instagram viral post, it’s not a sexy way to sell…. IT IS IMPORTANT. 

I became a trainer because I wanted to help women overcome the battles I felt, to build confidence and to remember WHY they really started. I became I trainer to try and use my platform to elevate and shine light on the importance of longevity and constant self care. 

Self care is pulling yourself out of a dark place and keeping your head held high even in moments you want to stop completely…. It’s not a face mask and bubble bath.

You have to keep going, keep pushing and not get swayed but a quick instant result and satisfaction. You have to prioritise you and remember how your fitness journey is there to elevate your life not consume it.

I hope this post makes you realise that when I say “I understand you” I really mean “ I got you and I have been there and you’ll get through it because I know you can” 

💙
